<TITLE> Primary students boycott school to protest abuse by teacher </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Barisal, July 11 (bdnews24.com)Students of a primary school in Nalchhiti Upazila have boycotted class for three days in protest of alleged molestation by a teacher, the school's headmaster made it public Wednesday. Ayub Hossain, head teacher of Miruhar Government Primary School in Magar Union, told reporters that students have not been attending class from July 9. He said girls at the school have long been complaining against the teacher. "I personally talked to him, but to no avail." Nalchhiti Upazila Primary Education Officer Mafizur Rahman told bdnews24.com that official action against the accused teacher was already underway. The head teacher said guardians of the students agreed to send their children to school Thursday on assurance of action against the accused teacher. The head teacher said the accused teacher has been on leave since Monday. bdnews24
